{
  "id": "L16",
  "title": "Returning a Faulty Product to a Store",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "In this lesson, you'll learn how to return a broken item to a store. Let's start by explaining the problem to a staff member."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L16_E01",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Pardon",
        "meaning": "Excuse me"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L16_E02",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ik heb een vraag",
        "meaning": "I have a question"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L16_V01",
      "data": {
        "Het product": "The product"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L16_E03",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ik heb ... gekocht",
        "meaning": "I have bought ..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L16_V02",
      "data": {
        "Het koffiezetapparaat": "The coffee machine"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L16_P01",
      "data": {
        "word": "koffiezetapparaat",
        "phonetic": "KOF-fie-zet-ap-pa-raat",
        "tip": "This is a long compound word. Break it down: koffie (coffee) + zet (put) + apparaat (apparatus)."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L16_V03",
      "data": {
        "Hier": "Here"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L16_V04",
      "data": {
        "Vorige week": "Last week"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L16_V05",
      "data": {
        "Kapot": "Broken"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L16_E04",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Het is ...",
        "meaning": "It is ..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L16_E05",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Dat is niet goed",
        "meaning": "That is not good"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L16_S01",
      "title": "Explaining the problem",
      "setting": "You are in an electronics store. You approach an employee to explain an issue with a product you bought.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Get the employee's attention and state you have a question about a product.",
          "chatbot_message": "Hallo."
        },
        {
          "title": "Explain that you bought the coffee machine here last week.",
          "chatbot_message": "Oké, een vraag over een product. Zeg het maar."
        },
        {
          "title": "State that the product is broken.",
          "chatbot_message": "Oké, vorige week. En?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Great start! Now you need to show your proof of purchase and suggest a solution. In Dutch shops, this is 'het bonnetje'."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L16_E06",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Heeft u...?",
        "meaning": "Do you have...?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L16_V06",
      "data": {
        "Het bonnetje": "The receipt"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L16_P02",
      "data": {
        "word": "bonnetje",
        "phonetic": "BON-nuh-tye",
        "tip": "The '-tje' at the end is a diminutive, so this literally means 'little receipt'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L16_E07",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Hier is...",
        "meaning": "Here is..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L16_E08",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Dank u",
        "meaning": "Thank you (formal)"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Use 'dank u' when speaking to staff or people you don't know. It's more formal and polite than 'dank je'."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L16_E09",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ik wil graag...",
        "meaning": "I would like..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L16_V07",
      "data": {
        "Een nieuwe": "A new one"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L16_V08",
      "data": {
        "Of": "Or"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L16_E10",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Mijn geld terug",
        "meaning": "My money back"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L16_S02",
      "title": "Proposing a solution",
      "setting": "You've explained the problem. Now the employee is asking for more information.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Show them the receipt.",
          "chatbot_message": "Oh, dat is niet goed. Heeft u het bonnetje?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Say that you would like a new one.",
          "chatbot_message": "Dank u."
        },
        {
          "title": "As an alternative, ask for your money back.",
          "chatbot_message": "Oké."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Excellent! Let's finish the conversation. The employee will offer a solution. You just need to agree and say thanks."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L16_E11",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Alstublieft",
        "meaning": "Here you go / Please"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L16_E12",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Dat is goed",
        "meaning": "That is good"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L16_E13",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Alles is in orde",
        "meaning": "Everything is in order / sorted out"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L16_V09",
      "data": {
        "De hulp": "The help"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L16_E14",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Dank u voor de hulp",
        "meaning": "Thank you for the help"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L16_V10",
      "data": {
        "Mooi": "Nice / Good"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L16_E15",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Graag gedaan",
        "meaning": "You're welcome"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "'Graag gedaan' is the most common reply to 'dank u' or 'dank je'."
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L16_S03",
      "title": "Resolving the issue",
      "setting": "The employee has heard your request and is now offering you a solution.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Respond positively to their solution of getting a new machine.",
          "chatbot_message": "Oké. Hier is een nieuwe. Alstublieft."
        },
        {
          "title": "Confirm that everything is now sorted out.",
          "chatbot_message": "Oké."
        },
        {
          "title": "Thank them for the help.",
          "chatbot_message": "Mooi."
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}